description: Extension to time limit of 06/1652 for mixed-use purposes, comprising Class A1 retail (with a replacement Oriental City including a Sui Generis amusement arcade and A3/A5 Uses, new B & Q and bulky goods store, together should provide 500 jobs), 520 residential units (comprising 1, 2 and 3-bedroom flats, 4% affordable) located in eight blocks rising to 3, 6, 9 and 18 storeys above a fifth-floor-level landscaped podium along the Edgware Road, rising to 8, 4, 5 and 2 storeys above the fifth-floor landscaped podium facing Plaza Walk and rising to 3 and 6 storeys above the Grove Park street level; a nursery and primary school for 480 children, a health & fitness studio (Use Class D2), associated landscaping, servicing, 1,098 car-parking spaces, comprising 721 spaces for retail users (incl. school drop-off and disabled), 5 staff spaces accessed from Grove Park for the school, and 351 (incl. disabled) spaces for residents and a further 21 disabled spaces on the podium and works to highway.
